<h3>Remarks:</h3>
<blockquote>
<em>2011-Apr-12 12:28:35 by matt:</em> <br>

Note: Failure of PRE (non-zero return) followed by success of POST (zero return) would properly result in the job being skipped.

<p><hr>
<em>2011-May-18 09:23:11 by nwp:</em> <br>

Does this include the case from <span class="ticket"><a href="tktview?tn=2122" class="resolved"
title="Allow PRE script to skip node job"
>#2122</a></span>?

<p><hr>
<em>2011-May-18 11:54:18 by matt:</em> <br>

I believe it does, in Logan's case his PRE script would simply fail, meaning the job is not run. The POST script would then check for the output and succeed (skip) or fail the node. The solution here does not require extending the DAGMan language.

<p><hr>
<em>2011-May-26 21:07:43 by nwp:</em> <br>

The patch attached to this ticket now implements a config option to restore the current behavior of skipping the POST script if the PRE script fails.

<p><hr>
<em>2011-Jun-06 06:29:29 by nwp:</em> <br>

New attachment 2057-patch-2 should be used, as there is a conflict with <span class="ticket"><a href="tktview?tn=1755" class="resolved"
title="Have a -strict flag that turns some warnings into fatal errors"
>#1755</a></span> in the former patch.

<p><hr>
<em>2011-Jun-14 22:13:38 by nwp:</em> <br>

Pushed my development branch to the central repository, at branch <code>V7_7-always_run_post_script_even_if_pre_script_fails-branch</code>.

<p><hr>
<em>2011-Jul-14 17:29:07 by wenger:</em> <br>

I haven't looked at everything yet, but here are comments on what I've reviewed so far:

<p>Retries should not short-circuit the POST script!  (In Dag::PreScriptReaper()
the check for whether to run the POST script if the PRE script failed
has to come before the check for node retries.)

<p>When running the POST script, I don't think that job-&gt;_scriptPost-&gt;_retValJob
should be set to DAG_ERROR_CONDOR_SUBMIT_FAILED (that means that
the condor_submit command itself failed).  I think that
job-&gt;_scriptPost-&gt;_retValJob should be set to the return value of the
PRE script.

<p>The A test should delete the dagman.out file at the beginning.

<p>The B test should check to make sure POST script was not run (in the
failure subroutine).

<p>There should probably be a test that combines this functionality with
node retries.

<p>I don't like the name 'NoPostRun' for the command-line argument -- it makes
it sound like the post script will never be run.  How about 'PostIgnorePre'?

<p>Dag::ProcessJobProcEnd(), Dag::ProcessFailedSubmit() and
Dag::PreScriptReaper() have pretty much duplicated code for running the
POST script -- this could be broken out into a little method to avoid
duplication.

<p>This is a pretty important change, so it needs to be well documented.  I
can think of at least four places that need changes:

<p><pre>
  * The version history.
  * The configuration section.
  * The condor_dagman and condor_submit_dag man pages.
  * The main DAGMan manual section.
</pre>

<p><hr>
<em>2011-Jul-14 17:42:23 by wenger:</em> <br>

Okay, I've finished checking -- no more comments...

